      Modifier and Type Method and Description

      Close the connection in a normal way

      Connect function this takes all default or set information about the client and attempts to connect and start a connection with the main

      get thread pool, for internal usage

      Send a packet over a channel to the main
      FireIoClient send(java.lang.String channel, java.lang.String message)
      Send a message (string) over a channel to the main
      FireIoClient setAutoReConnect(int timeout)
      Sets and enables the auto reconnect for the client This means that when the connection dies or gets disrupted the client will try to re-connect after a set amount of milliseconds
      FireIoClient setMeta(java.lang.String s, ClientMeta meta)
      Set a meta data tag can be used to supply extra information mid handshake (like client location or device information)
      FireIoClient setPassword(java.lang.String password)
      Set the password to connect to the main only has effect before the connect() function is called
      FireIoClient setTag(java.lang.String s, java.lang.String b)
      Set a tag, this can be used by the main API to identify clients works like a username
      FireIoClient setThreadPoolSize(int size)
      Set the thread pool size used to execute events All events are ASYNC by default default is 1
      FireIoClient stop()
      Another way to close the client, effectively the same as close();
